node.text: This Plum Galette from Chef Jacques Pépin is a rustic tart with an elegant finish. The buttery, flaky pâte brisée dough gets filled with fresh, seasonal fruit and baked until richly browned in the oven. A final brushing of fruit preserves provides flavorful and beautiful sheen. Tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.text: The inspiration for this Spicy Tofu and Zucchini Stew that @annie.h.shi makes for cozy weeknight dinners every season of the year comes from Soondubu Jjigae, a spicy Korean tofu stew, that she grew up eating at restaurants. The recipe features an umami-rich broth powered by dashi packets, gochugaru, doenjang (fermented soybean paste), and gochujang. Tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.text: “I think this cookie is so elegant and so New York chic and I’m gonna take it to SoHo,” says Chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) as she adds gold leaf to her take on the classic Black and White cookie. Bling aside, these Black and Ruby Cookies are already extra special with ruby chocolate instead of white, buttermilk instead of whole, and rye flour as a nod to iconic NYC deli breads. Find out how to make them by visiting this link:https://bit.ly/3zD88fk or tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.title: Pastries with Paola | Black and Ruby Cookies

Tap the link in bio for this a-maize-ing recipe!

node.text: Our 2021 class of Best New Chefs is finally here! Representing the East Coast we have chefs Angel Barreto, Lucas Sin and Paola Velez. Angel Barreto (@angellbarreto) is a lifelong student of Korean food who pushes boundaries with menus that look to both past and future for inspiration. Lucas Sin (@lucas.sin) is on a mission to take a delicious deep dive into changing the perception of American Chinese food with an eye toward sustainability when it comes to people, their mental health and their finances. Meanwhile Paola Velez (@smallorchids) strives to improve kitchen culture and help make the hospitality industry a more fair and equitable place all while making by bold, vibrant desserts and maintaining an unmatched energy, humor and enthusiasm. Meet these three Best New Chefs, along with the rest of the members of the 2021 class, through the link in bio. #FWBNC

node.text: Our 2021 class of Best New Chefs is finally here! Representing the west coast we have chefs Carlo Lamagna, Gaby Maeda, Matt Horn, and Thessa Diadem. Matt horn (@matthornx) is a self-taught pit master who’s never worked in any restaurant but his own and is now solely dedicated to creating a unique, personal, and delicious style of barbecue. Gaby Maeda (@gmaeda25) is drawing inspiration from her Honolulu childhood to create a menu that is part Hawaiian, part Californian, and entirely her own. Meanwhile Thessa Diadem (@thessa.diadem) is getting inspired by the international grocery stores around her and channeling them into innovative, decadent pastries that look just as good as they taste. For Carlo Lamagna (@twistedfilipino) cooking is an homage to the vibrant flavors of his childhood in the Philippines as well as a tribute to his late father and community. Meet these four Best New Chefs, along with the rest of the members of the 2021 class, through the link in bio. #FWBNC

node.text: From coast to coast, the 2021 class of Best New Chefs is reinventing what it means to lead in the kitchen while cooking the food that matters to them most. Restaurants may no longer look the same, but with this class of chefs at the helm, we’re excited to see—and eat—what the future holds. Meet the 2021 Food & Wine Best New Chefs through the link in bio. Words and winners by @khushandoj. #FWBNC #sponsored

node.text: 7 weeks on the road, 18 cities, 1,600 miles driven, 90+ restaurants, and 66 ginger ales—that’s what it took our Restaurant Editor @khushandoj to arrive at our 2021 class of Food & Wine Best New Chefs. Keep an eye on our platforms to find out who they are.

node.text: This recipe for Spicy Fried Rice-Stuffed Chicken Wings from 2019 F&W Best New Chef @jparkato features chicken wings dredged in a crackling fried chicken breading and stuffed with spicy, savory doubanjiang fried rice. The final touch is a tongue-tingling spice blend of Szechuan peppercorn, salt, sugar, and powdered vinegar. Tap the link in bio to get the recipe! 📸: @gregdupree

node.text:
Every online grocery delivery service has the same concept: delivering groceries to your doorstep—but varies in pricing, product offerings, and principles. From budget-friendly to organic, plant-based and everything in between, we rounded up the 10 best online grocery delivery services so you can get the food you want without stepping out of the house. Tap the link in bio to start shopping!
📸: @hellofresh

node.text: Buttery, spicy and fresh with a hint of lime, these shrimp are reminiscent of street food inspired by 2019 F&W Best New Chef @chefkwameonwuachi's travels in Jamaica. Fresh ginger and Scotch bonnet peppers infuse Kwame's Pepper Shrimp with layers of heat and flavor. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 📸: Caitlin Bensel

node.text: On this episode of Chefs At Home, Chicago sommelier @derrickcwestbrook of @juice_1340 creates a symphony of flavors as he prepares a simple Italian dish, Creamy Tomato Rigatoni, and pairs it with an unexpected wine, Austrian Blaufränkisch. Westbrook also engages all the senses with a classical music playlist that is a perfect accompaniment to the duo. Tap the link in bio to watch the entire episode on YouTube!

node.text: Whether you like your tacos packed with meat, seafood, or vegetables, we've included 30 taco recipes to put into your rotation. Our favorites include classics like birria and carne asada tacos as well as plant-powered kale and crispy potato ones. Click the link in our bio to discover which tacos recipes you'll want to bookmark for later! 📸: @caitbensel

node.text: If you need inspiration for pasta night, we have you covered for almost every week of the year. Rigatoni! Spaghetti! Gnocchi! Whether you're looking for a quick meal, a weekend project or a one-pot wonder, these pasta recipes won't let you down. Tap the link in bio to discover some of our favorites! 📸: @protazio

node.text:
We usually advise against burning baked goods but to make F&W 2020 Best New Chef @tavel19's Basque Cheesecake recipe properly, you’re going to have to let it burn. The end result is a perfectly creamy cake with an intense, deeply caramelized top. It's best enjoyed plain, but a dark berry fruit preserve or compote pairs well too. Baking tips and the recipe are linked in our bio! 
📸: @cedricangeles
